<p><strong>Username:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1523276175" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span></p>
<p><strong>Experience:</strong> IRL, I'm a QA Coordinator/Supervisor for a billion-dollar company out of Atlanta. Most of the work I do concerns meeting product specifications for our customers, as well as setting material specifications with our suppliers and working with end users to find acceptable solutions to issues they are having with their product. I singlehandedly process, approve, and resolve upwards on $100K worth of claims each week.</p>
<p>At the same time, I also help manage our QA department, including training, hands-on development of testing protocols, and working with our product development engineers to create new technologies in our field while still meeting customer standards and safety regulations. I additionally manage requisitions for both myself and my department, frequently managing thousands of dollars worth of materials and supplies each week.</p>
<p>Lastly, I'm also the Lead Auditor for our ISO Team, and am in charge of making sure our facility meets all of the standards of ISO 9001. In doing so, I also act as our Plant Management Representative, working with our customers and suppliers to meet required regulatory standards, etc. I also help lead our Food Safety Team, as well as our Job Safety Initiative and Social Outreach teams.</p>
<p><strong>Professional Experience:</strong> See above. TL;DR: Quality Management.</p>
<p><strong>Any professional accolades, certifications, or qualifications for this skill set:</strong> ISO 9001 certification, ISO 22000 certification, OSHA certification, various food and job safety certifications, etc.</p>
<p><strong>What technologies are you familiar with in your area?</strong> Admittedly my IT experience is minimal at best, and since my experience is almost completely devoted to manufacturing my best talents worth bringing to the table are in QA personnel management and supervisory leadership, unless you're planning on managing the project on Oracle's JD Edwards E1 in which case are we actually building a website or are we instead getting into plastics.</p>
<p>That being said, we manage our QA process on about a half dozen different systems, each of which I've had to become proficient with in a relatively short period of time, so I'm sure we could make it work.</p>

