<p><strong>Username:</strong> Hollows</p>
<p><strong>Experience:</strong> I am an IT professional with 4 years of experience in system administration, technical support, and information management. Experience maintaining 24/7/365 and/or 100% availability systems for local and state governments, in addition to creating custom solutions for customers using a variety of technologies depending on the customer's needs.</p>
<p><strong>Professional Experience:</strong> I have experience in a number of IT roles, almost all with government systems. One of my previous roles consisted of primarily tier one IT support, including customer support, router ans switch maintenance, 0365 and Exchange maintenance, server administration, AP installation, VLAN configuration, etc. Another role was in IT project management, converting outdated organization frameworks to modern ITIL, ServiceNow, and Jira frameworks where applicable.</p>
<p>My most recent role included all aforementioned tier one duties with the addition of some IT management, including creating additions to the business continuity plan and disaster recovery plan. In this role, I also managed certain parts of FOIA requests, maintaining content that should be available to the public 100% of the time to comply with government oversight and transparency law.</p>
<p>Technical documentation is a specialty of mine. I have been hired before based solely on the quality of my documentation and technical writing.</p>
<p><strong>Any professional accolades, certifications, or qualifications for this skill set:</strong> bachelor's degree in Information Technology w/ magna cum laude honors from my program. Was president of local association of IT professionals for two years, expert with networking and coordination.</p>
<p><strong>What technologies are you familiar with in your area?:</strong> I am familiar with a myriad of resource management and issue tracking systems, such as ServiceNow, Jira, KACE, and custom tracking solutions based on O365 SharePoint and WordPress. Experience with Docker, PowerShell, Bash, Kubernetes, and VMWare for the fully automated creation, configuration, and implementation of containerized VMs with 0 downtime. Creation and maintenance of containerized full-stack Elasticsearch-Logstash-Kibana data collection and visualization system.</p>

